{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Translation table: Rocksmith gear knob → VST parameter mapping. Read by GET /vst/knob_mapping and applied by the per-piece 'Apply RS settings' button + rbReapplyVstParamsAfterLoad. Curated against the free VST recommendations in rs_gear_to_vst.json.",
    "version": 2,
    "updated": "2026-05-28",
    "schema": {
      "<rs_gear_type>": {
        "<vst_name_stem_lowercased>": {
          "<rs_knob_name>": {
            "param": "<exact VST param name as shown in the in-app editor>",
            "scale": "<float, multiply RS value by this. 0.01 for 0-100 → 0-1; 0.0005 for ms 0-2000>",
            "offset": "<optional float, added after scale>",
            "invert": "<optional bool, replaces v with (1-v) after scale>",
            "min": "<optional float, clamp lower>",
            "max": "<optional float, clamp upper>"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "notes": [
      "VST param names are best-effort. If a mapping doesn't take, open the in-app VST editor for that gear, copy the exact param name from a slider, and paste here.",
      "Default RS knob range is 0-100 → use scale=0.01 to land in the VST's 0-1 normalized range.",
      "Time knobs are in ms (e.g. 320ms). Most VST delay 'Time' params are normalized 0-1 representing a max ms range — check the VST's docs and set scale accordingly.",
      "EQ pedals (EQ5/EQ8) store knobs as frequency strings (e.g. '5700') with the value being dB gain at that frequency. Can't auto-map cleanly to a 4-band dynamic EQ — leave empty and tweak per song."
    ]
  },

  "Pedal_Chorus": {
